				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well the problem with those two is that you can make a new one of each easily, so it's rather hard to make the augments stick with them.
<br />

<br />
Mage epic is summonable, although I don't believe it's norent.  Might be wrong with that tho.
<br />

<br />
Warrior epic is actually created.  You get your epic from a combine.  The quest gets you a red sword sheath (4-slot container), and two blades and two hilts...combine the two hilts and two blades in the sheath, and you get a brand-new sheath with the epics.  This new red sheath is different than the one you combined the epics in.  If I remember right, if you put a mage-summoned Sword of Runes into this second red sheath and hit combine (this does not work with the pre-final combine red sheath), you can get 2 more warrior epic 1handers. (meaning you turn the epic into the 2hander and put the sword of runes into the sheath and you can have both the 2hander and the two 1handers.
<br />

<br />
So with Mage and Warrior, you have an epic where they can create a new one...so the system needs to be different for those two items.<br />_________________<br />Bow to others in reverence and respect, but never in slavery.
<br />
~Raistlin Majere~
